<p>Oklahoma presents an exceptional opportunity for homeowners considering solar panels and HVAC system upgrades, combining abundant sunshine with reasonable electricity costs and supportive utility policies. With an average of 5.1 sun hours per day throughout the year, the Sooner State ranks among the top solar resource states in the nation, providing consistent energy production potential that makes solar installations highly viable. The state's relatively low electricity rates of approximately 10.5¬¢ per kWh, primarily served by Oklahoma Gas & Electric (OG&E), create a stable baseline for calculating solar savings and return on investment.</p>

